can't change the past,
or punish someone else,

00:15:35.820 --> 00:15:37.960 align:middle line:90%
but they can hurt you.

00:15:37.960 --> 00:15:38.760 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:15:38.760 --> 00:15:40.380 align:middle line:90%
That's what we suffer from.

00:15:40.380 --> 00:15:41.770 align:middle line:90%
We suffer from our anger.

00:15:41.770 --> 00:15:43.170 align:middle line:90%
We suffer from our pain.

00:15:43.170 --> 00:15:45.870 align:middle line:84%
We suffer from our fear
of the past of what

00:15:45.870 --> 00:15:48.960 align:middle line:84%
has-- our pain in the past, and
our fear of the future of what

00:15:48.960 --> 00:15:49.950 align:middle line:90%
is or isn't going to.

00:15:49.950 --> 00:15:52.800 align:middle line:84%
So it's really the reality
that the past is gone.

00:15:52.800 --> 00:15:54.600 align:middle line:84%
It really remains
in our heads only.

00:15:54.600 --> 00:15:56.100 align:middle line:84%
The future is never
going to happen.

00:15:56.100 --> 00:15:58.845 align:middle line:84%
It's only a thought system that
actually becomes the present.

00:15:58.845 --> 00:15:59.645 align:middle line:90%
>> Be in the now.

00:15:59.645 --> 00:16:02.160 align:middle line:84%
>> So I want to respect the
future so that when it does

00:16:02.160 --> 00:16:04.620 align:middle line:84%
become the present, it
doesn't turn into chaos.

00:16:04.620 --> 00:16:06.530 align:middle line:84%
So it's about really
honoring the present.

00:16:06.530 --> 00:16:09.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Or making it more graphic,
it's like taking arsenic

00:16:09.010 --> 00:16:11.020 align:middle line:84%
and expecting
someone else to die.

00:16:11.020 --> 00:16:11.820 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:16:11.820 --> 00:16:12.420 align:middle line:90%
That's true.

00:16:12.420 --> 00:16:12.900 align:middle line:90%
That is.

00:16:12.900 --> 00:16:14.670 align:middle line:84%
Like, because you're
so angry at them.

00:16:14.670 --> 00:16:14.940 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:16:14.940 --> 00:16:15.560 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:16:15.560 --> 00:16:16.470 align:middle line:90%
And they may be going on.

00:16:16.470 --> 00:16:17.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:16:17.170 --> 00:16:18.960 align:middle line:84%
They might not even be here
anymore and not even know

00:16:18.960 --> 00:16:19.770 align:middle line:90%
you're upset with them.

00:16:19.770 --> 00:16:20.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:16:20.610 --> 00:16:21.410 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:16:21.410 --> 00:16:23.160 align:middle line:84%
You can see the
value of giving up

00:16:23.160 --> 00:16:25.840 align:middle line:84%
not some but all
of your judgments.

00:16:25.840 --> 00:16:26.910 align:middle line:90%
Hmm.

00:16:26.910 --> 00:16:28.630 align:middle line:90%
That is a stepping stone.

00:16:28.630 --> 00:16:29.430 align:middle line:90%
>> A major one.

00:16:29.430 --> 00:16:31.760 align:middle line:90%
We know a woman who at 90--

00:16:31.760 --> 00:16:32.790 align:middle line:90%
we met her at 94.

00:16:32.790 --> 00:16:34.950 align:middle line:84%
At 87, she completely
changed her life.

00:16:34.950 --> 00:16:36.210 align:middle line:90%
An extraordinary woman.

00:16:36.210 --> 00:16:38.270 align:middle line:84%
And when we asked her,
what is it about your--

00:16:38.270 --> 00:16:41.587 align:middle line:84%
what is it about you
that has shifted so much?

00:16:41.587 --> 00:16:42.670 align:middle line:90%
And she just looked at us.

00:16:42.670 --> 00:16:43.210 align:middle line:90%
Remember, Gerry?

00:16:43.210 --> 00:16:44.010 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:16:44.010 --> 00:16:46.410 align:middle line:84%
>> And she was from
Finland, and she said,

00:16:46.410 --> 00:16:49.200 align:middle line:90%
I just gave up all my judgments.

00:16:49.200 --> 00:16:52.620 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't mean we give
up our ability to evaluate

00:16:52.620 --> 00:16:54.120 align:middle line:90%
or our thinking powers.

00:16:54.120 --> 00:16:56.120 align:middle line:84%
The difference is, you
can evaluate objectively,

00:16:56.120 --> 00:16:58.095 align:middle line:84%
and many of us are
paid to evaluate.

00:16:58.095 --> 00:17:00.220 align:middle line:84%
We train a lot of social
workers, et cetera, people

00:17:00.220 --> 00:17:02.500 align:middle line:90%
who, that's your responsibility.

00:17:02.500 --> 00:17:04.883 align:middle line:84%
That's different than
making judgments on people.

00:17:04.883 --> 00:17:07.050 align:middle line:84%
>> And we're talking about
judgements like character

00:17:07.050 --> 00:17:07.950 align:middle line:90%
assassination.

00:17:07.950 --> 00:17:08.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Uh-huh.

00:17:08.750 --> 00:17:11.450 align:middle line:84%
>> It's really possible to see
the light in people rather than

00:17:11.450 --> 00:17:14.619 align:middle line:84%
the lampshade, and we
need to stop looking

00:17:14.619 --> 00:17:16.911 align:middle line:84%
at people's behavior and
recognize that people are

00:17:16.911 --> 00:17:19.369 align:middle line:84%
either loving or that they're
fearful and giving out a call

00:17:19.369 --> 00:17:20.280 align:middle line:90%
of help for love.

00:17:20.280 --> 00:17:22.150 align:middle line:84%
And this really forms the
basis of attitudinal healing

00:17:22.150 --> 00:17:23.270 align:middle line:84%
is all about, changing
our perceptions.

00:17:23.270 --> 00:17:25.098 align:middle line:84%
>> And if you can
step back from that,

00:17:25.098 --> 00:17:27.390 align:middle line:84%
and you can see that that is
where they're coming from,

00:17:27.390 --> 00:17:30.380 align:middle line:84%
they're coming from fear, then
it is easier to forgive them--

00:17:30.380 --> 00:17:31.180 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:17:31.180 --> 00:17:32.505 align:middle line:90%
>> --once you can be detached?

00:17:32.505 --> 00:17:33.090 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh yes.

00:17:33.090 --> 00:17:33.560 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:17:33.560 --> 00:17:34.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Our heart will accept
them when we do that.

00:17:34.990 --> 00:17:35.540 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:17:35.540 --> 00:17:37.460 align:middle line:84%
One can recognize that
holding onto anger

00:17:37.460 --> 00:17:40.370 align:middle line:84%
will not bring you
what you truly want.

00:17:40.370 --> 00:17:42.610 align:middle line:84%
There isn't really a payoff
for that anger, is there?

00:17:42.610 --> 00:17:45.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it's a good
question to ask ourselves.

00:17:45.110 --> 00:17:48.440 align:middle line:84%
Does holding on to what I
think is justified anger really

00:17:48.440 --> 00:17:49.970 align:middle line:90%
bring me peace of mind?

00:17:49.970 --> 00:17:52.693 align:middle line:84%
And I think everyone's going
to say, no, not really,

00:17:52.693 --> 00:17:55.235 align:middle line:84%
and begin to say, well, I don't
want to hold on to that then.

00:17:55.235 --> 00:17:59.175 align:middle line:84%
>> And oftentimes it takes time,
although we don't realize that

00:17:59.175 --> 00:18:01.245 align:middle line:84%
we're the ones that
determine the time.

00:18:01.245 --> 00:18:02.870 align:middle line:84%
And so if you think
it's going to take,

00:18:02.870 --> 00:18:04.370 align:middle line:84%
you know, a year
to get over this,

00:18:04.370 --> 00:18:05.745 align:middle line:90%
then it's going to take a year.

00:18:05.745 --> 00:18:06.620 align:middle line:90%
>> It'll take a year.

00:18:06.620 --> 00:18:08.537 align:middle line:84%
>> If you think it's
going to take six months,

00:18:08.537 --> 00:18:10.858 align:middle line:84%
if you think it'll never
happen, it will never happen.

00:18:10.858 --> 00:18:12.650 align:middle line:84%
If you believe that
it's possible to happen

00:18:12.650 --> 00:18:14.692 align:middle line:84%
in an instant, then it
will happen in an instant.

00:18:14.692 --> 00:18:16.460 align:middle line:90%
There's no schedule for anybody.

00:18:16.460 --> 00:18:18.890 align:middle line:10%
It's just that, for each
of us to become aware

00:18:18.890 --> 00:18:22.280 align:middle line:10%
that we have a tremendous
amount of input and power

00:18:22.280 --> 00:18:24.358 align:middle line:10%
over the course
of our own lives--

00:18:24.358 --> 00:18:26.150 align:middle line:10%
not necessarily what
happens on the outside

00:18:26.150 --> 00:18:28.525 align:middle line:10%
all the time, because a lot
of that we don't have control

00:18:28.525 --> 00:18:30.470 align:middle line:10%
over, but what we
do have control over

00:18:30.470 --> 00:18:32.990 align:middle line:10%
are the thoughts and
attitudes and judgments

00:18:32.990 --> 00:18:36.463 align:middle line:10%
and perceptions and projections
that are inside of us.

00:18:36.463 --> 00:18:37.880 align:middle line:84%
>> And you know,
it's interesting.

00:18:37.880 --> 00:18:39.470 align:middle line:84%
There are terrible
things that happen,

00:18:39.470 --> 00:18:41.780 align:middle line:84%
and there are people
that do awful things,

00:18:41.780 --> 00:18:46.580 align:middle line:84%
and we have to just recall
that, that it isn't condoning.

00:18:46.580 --> 00:18:47.760 align:middle line:90%
Again, it is just forgiving.

00:18:47.760 --> 00:18:48.560 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:18:48.560 --> 00:18:49.990 align:middle line:90%
>> And stepping back from it.

00:18:49.990 --> 00:18:51.890 align:middle line:84%
>> And it doesn't mean that you
don't go out and do something

00:18:51.890 --> 00:18:54.557 align:middle line:84%
about it, but it means you don't
come from the place of your own

00:18:54.557 --> 00:18:56.870 align:middle line:84%
anger and multiplying the
anger, as I mentioned before.

00:18:56.870 --> 00:19:00.095 align:middle line:84%
It means that, once you have
found your own responsibility,

00:19:00.095 --> 00:19:01.970 align:middle line:84%
you say, what do I need
to think, say, and do

00:19:01.970 --> 00:19:03.050 align:middle line:90%
about this situation?

00:19:03.050 --> 00:19:04.735 align:middle line:84%
And then, go out on
the world and do it.

00:19:04.735 --> 00:19:07.152 align:middle line:84%
>> A couple of years ago, we
were involved in a conference

00:19:07.152 --> 00:19:09.350 align:middle line:84%
in Bosnia with religious
and spiritual leaders,

00:19:09.350 --> 00:19:11.180 align:middle line:84%
and forgiveness
and reconciliation.

00:19:11.180 --> 00:19:15.000 align:middle line:84%
And there was this one priest
that shared going to his house

00:19:15.000 --> 00:19:15.800 align:middle line:90%
and saw it burning.

00:19:15.800 --> 00:19:16.440 align:middle line:90%
Remember that?

00:19:16.440 --> 00:19:17.240 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:19:17.240 --> 00:19:18.770 align:middle line:84%
His-- he was from
Serbia, actually,

00:19:18.770 --> 00:19:21.570 align:middle line:84%
and the Bosnians had taken
his parents, grandparents,

00:19:21.570 --> 00:19:24.530 align:middle line:84%
and four siblings in a house,
sealed it up, and torched it,

00:19:24.530 --> 00:19:27.140 align:middle line:84%
and he said at the moment
that he saw that, he

00:19:27.140 --> 00:19:28.880 align:middle line:90%
realized he had two choices.

00:19:28.880 --> 00:19:31.490 align:middle line:84%
He was either going to spend the
rest of his life hunting them

00:19:31.490 --> 00:19:33.350 align:middle line:84%
down and be one of
them, or he'd have

00:19:33.350 --> 00:19:36.140 align:middle line:90%
to learn somehow to forgive.

00:19:36.140 --> 00:19:38.240 align:middle line:84%
And we found him, of
course, as a Serbian priest.

00:19:38.240 --> 00:19:39.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:19:39.040 --> 00:19:40.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Powerful story.

00:19:40.310 --> 00:19:42.122 align:middle line:90%
>> Powerful.

00:19:42.122 --> 00:19:42.950 align:middle line:90%
Ooh.

00:19:42.950 --> 00:19:45.920 align:middle line:84%
Now, see that there is no
value in punishing yourself,

00:19:45.920 --> 00:19:48.490 align:middle line:84%
that it's a gift to
ourselves if we do forgive.

00:19:48.490 --> 00:19:49.290 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:19:49.290 --> 00:19:49.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:19:49.770 --> 00:19:52.145 align:middle line:84%
>> Gerry, talk about that pill
that you often talk about.

00:19:52.145 --> 00:19:55.450 align:middle line:90%
If somebody had a pill that--?

00:19:55.450 --> 00:19:56.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:19:56.250 --> 00:19:57.440 align:middle line:90%
I think I remember.

00:19:57.440 --> 00:19:58.600 align:middle line:90%
The pill.

00:19:58.600 --> 00:20:01.585 align:middle line:84%
If you read on your TV
program that a pill had

00:20:01.585 --> 00:20:03.600 align:middle line:84%
been just invented
that's guaranteed

00:20:03.600 --> 00:20:05.700 align:middle line:84%
to take away all the
anger that we ever

00:20:05.700 --> 00:20:11.922 align:middle line:84%
had, all of our
judgments, and it's free.

00:20:11.922 --> 00:20:13.130 align:middle line:90%
>> There are no side effects.

00:20:13.130 --> 00:20:13.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:20:13.610 --> 00:20:14.410 align:middle line:90%
No side effects.

00:20:14.410 --> 00:20:17.250 align:middle line:84%
We'd run and get it, and this
is really what forgiveness does.

00:20:17.250 --> 00:20:17.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Ah.

00:20:17.640 --> 00:20:19.662 align:middle line:84%
>> The decision to, and
willingness to, forgive.

00:20:19.662 --> 00:20:22.120 align:middle line:84%
>> That's why you'll write that
prescription, I understand,

00:20:22.120 --> 00:20:22.390 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:20:22.390 --> 00:20:23.320 align:middle line:90%
>> Prescription for peace.

00:20:23.320 --> 00:20:23.785 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:20:23.785 --> 00:20:24.250 align:middle line:90%
You got it.

00:20:24.250 --> 00:20:25.080 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:20:25.080 --> 00:20:27.680 align:middle line:84%
And we can choose to be
happy rather than right.

00:20:27.680 --> 00:20:28.480 align:middle line:90%
Ah-ha.

00:20:28.480 --> 00:20:28.940 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:20:28.940 --> 00:20:31.150 align:middle line:84%
>> And that's right in the
sense that-- of righteousness.

00:20:31.150 --> 00:20:31.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:20:31.520 --> 00:20:33.120 align:middle line:84%
>> That in other
words, if I'm right,

00:20:33.120 --> 00:20:35.330 align:middle line:84%
that means I have to make
sure that you're wrong.

00:20:35.330 --> 00:20:36.130 align:middle line:90%
>> Uh-huh.

00:20:36.130 --> 00:20:36.930 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:20:36.930 --> 00:20:38.430 align:middle line:90%
Making the other person wrong.

00:20:38.430 --> 00:20:39.930 align:middle line:84%
And believe that
you have the power

00:20:39.930 --> 00:20:42.180 align:middle line:84%
to choose the thoughts
you put into your mind.

00:20:42.180 --> 00:20:45.030 align:middle line:84%
So we really can control
those thoughts in our mind.

00:20:45.030 --> 00:20:47.710 align:middle line:84%
That's that practical
spirituality, even.

00:20:47.710 --> 00:20:48.510 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep.

00:20:48.510 --> 00:20:51.192 align:middle line:10%
That's what it's all about,
that no one else decides

00:20:51.192 --> 00:20:53.150 align:middle line:10%
what thoughts we put in
the body but ourselves,

00:20:53.150 --> 00:20:56.970 align:middle line:10%
and so meditation and being
prayerful, spending time

00:20:56.970 --> 00:21:00.450 align:middle line:10%
in nature, learning to
still the mind is some

00:21:00.450 --> 00:21:03.360 align:middle line:10%
of the ingredients that's
really important to begin

00:21:03.360 --> 00:21:06.510 align:middle line:10%
to discipline our minds so we
begin to have loving thoughts

00:21:06.510 --> 00:21:09.200 align:middle line:10%
rather than fearful
and attacking thoughts.

00:21:09.200 --> 00:21:10.950 align:middle line:84%
>> And you know, the
last one I just love.

00:21:10.950 --> 00:21:14.070 align:middle line:84%
Be willing to make peace
of mind your only goal,

00:21:14.070 --> 00:21:17.100 align:middle line:84%
and believe that forgiveness
is the key to happiness.

00:21:17.100 --> 00:21:19.420 align:middle line:84%
>> And everything else
can become our intentions.

00:21:19.420 --> 00:21:22.230 align:middle line:84%
But if you have multiple-- if
you have conflicting goals,

00:21:22.230 --> 00:21:23.820 align:middle line:84%
you're always going
to be in conflict.

00:21:23.820 --> 00:21:26.860 align:middle line:84%
Peace of mind means having
a harmony and integrity

00:21:26.860 --> 00:21:29.190 align:middle line:84%
in what you think, what
you say, what you do.

00:21:29.190 --> 00:21:30.690 align:middle line:90%
It's not being passive.

00:21:30.690 --> 00:21:33.727 align:middle line:84%
It's very active,
and very powerful.

00:21:33.727 --> 00:21:36.060 align:middle line:84%
>> It's really possible to
have peace of mind regardless

00:21:36.060 --> 00:21:37.530 align:middle line:84%
of what's happening
in the world.

00:21:37.530 --> 00:21:39.030 align:middle line:84%
We were in Hawaii
recently and there

00:21:39.030 --> 00:21:42.030 align:middle line:84%
was a person that's head of the
mental health department there,

00:21:42.030 --> 00:21:46.530 align:middle line:84%
and she stated that she found
that having peace of mind

00:21:46.530 --> 00:21:48.238 align:middle line:84%
was really the only
way that she can deal

00:21:48.238 --> 00:21:50.113 align:middle line:84%
with what was happening
outside, and that she

00:21:50.113 --> 00:21:51.200 align:middle line:90%
could choose to do that.

00:21:51.200 --> 00:21:52.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Ah.

00:21:52.000 --> 00:21:52.980 align:middle line:90%
That is so powerful.

00:21:52.980 --> 00:21:55.650 align:middle line:84%
It really is, and that
is being responsible

00:21:55.650 --> 00:21:56.640 align:middle line:90%
for our own happiness.

00:21:56.640 --> 00:21:58.350 align:middle line:84%
Well, bless you, and
thank you for the work

00:21:58.350 --> 00:22:00.683 align:middle line:84%
you are doing and sharing
your forgiveness with everyone

00:22:00.683 --> 00:22:02.460 align:middle line:84%
in the latest book,
"Simple Thoughts

00:22:02.460 --> 00:22:03.670 align:middle line:90%
That Can Change Your Life."

00:22:03.670 --> 00:22:06.130 align:middle line:90%
So blessings and thank you.

